"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419722","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Secretary of State is giving careful consideration to the inspector’s report on the inquiry into proposed extensions to the Lake District and Yorkshire Dales National Parks and will issue her decisions in due course.</p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2015-10-19T13:40:45.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419722/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419722/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419722/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-10-05","National Parks","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answers by Lord Gardiner of Kimble on 17 September (HL1861 and HL1991), what further steps remain in the process of taking a decision about extending the boundaries of the Lake District and Yorkshire Dales National Parks, and what timetable they have set for those further steps to be taken.","false","Biography information for Lord Judd",,"Lord Judd","HL2425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419723","Home Office","false","2015-10-19","<p>Figures on the number of people who have returned to the UK from all conflict zones are not available. However, the Police have estimated that around 700 people from the UK who are of concern are thought to have travelled to the Syria/Iraq region since the start of the conflict, and that around half of those have returned. All decisions on handling returnees from Syria or Iraq are taken on a case-by-case basis. For some, prosecution for terrorist offences is the right course of action, and this will be a decision for the police and the Crown Prosecution Service. For others, it may be that support from mental health or social services might be more appropriate.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-10-19T16:24:26.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419723/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419723/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419723/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-05","Armed Conflict: British Nationals Abroad","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many people aged (1) 21 and over, and (2) under 21, are known to have returned to the United Kingdom from a conflict zone since January 2014; and of those, how many were (a) charged with an offence and convicted, and (b) not charged but were put under supervision and entered into programmes of deradicalisation.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kennedy of The Shaws",,"Baroness Kennedy of The Shaws","HL2426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419724","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-29","<p>As of Friday 23 October, there were 94 prisoners convicted of or on remand for offences under Terrorism Act legislation in prisons in England and Wales. Of these, 85 are 21 and over, and 9 are under 21. Of these 94 prisoners, 2 have been released and subsequently recalled to prison since January 2014.</p><br /><p>Of the 94, 46 prisoners have undertaken the Extremism Risk Guidelines assessment. These assessments only occur when a prisoner has been convicted and settled in to prison. The Secretary of State has asked the department to review its approach to dealing with Islamist extremism in prisons and probation. This will be supported by external expertise and will sit alongside the cross government work currently underway on developing de-radicalisation programmes.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2015-10-29T12:28:30.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419724/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419724/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419724/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-05","Terrorism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many people aged (1) 21 and over, and (2) under 21, are currently in prison for a terrorist offence; of those, (a) how many have been released on licence since January 2014, and (b) how many have undergone a programme of resettlement or deradicalisation; and what information they have on the effectiveness of resettlement or deradicalisation programmes.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kennedy of The Shaws",,"Baroness Kennedy of The Shaws","HL2427"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419725","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-20","<p>Details of research commissioned by the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS), is not readily available and can only be obtained at disproportionate cost. BIS has published its research strategy and details of the monitoring and evaluation of its programmes. Details can be found at the ‘BIS evaluation strategy’ and ‘BIS research strategy’ sections of the GOV.UK website, which are attached.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-10-20T11:19:53.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419725/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419725/answer","evaluation-strategy-2015-16-accountability-and-learning-at-the-heart-of-bis.pdf ; Research_Strategy_2014-2015.pdf","evaluation-strategy-2015-16-accountability-and-learning-at-the-heart-of-bis.pdf ; Research_Strategy_2014-2015.pdf","Evaluation Strategy ; Research Strategy","Evaluation Strategy ; Research Strategy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419725/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-05","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Research","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much has been paid to external research and polling companies by the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills in each month since October 2014, and to which companies payments were made.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kramer",,"Baroness Kramer","HL2428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419726","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-20","<p>Details of research commissioned by the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS), is not readily available and can only be obtained at disproportionate cost. BIS has published its research strategy and details of the monitoring and evaluation of its programmes. Details can be found at the ‘BIS evaluation strategy’ and ‘BIS research strategy’ sections of the GOV.UK website, which are attached.</p><br />",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-10-20T12:53:20.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419726/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419726/answer","evaluation-strategy-2015-16-accountability-and-learning-at-the-heart-of-bis.pdf ; Research_Strategy_2014-2015.pdf","evaluation-strategy-2015-16-accountability-and-learning-at-the-heart-of-bis.pdf ; Research_Strategy_2014-2015.pdf","Evaluation Strategy ; Research Strategy","Evaluation Strategy ; Research Strategy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419726/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-05","Small businesses","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what research they have commissioned from external research and polling companies on small business policies in each month since May.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kramer",,"Baroness Kramer","HL2429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419727","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-12","<p>This information is not held centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate costs.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-10-12T11:07:09.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419727/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419727/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419727/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-05","Small Businesses","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many meetings (1) the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, (2) ministers within the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills, and (3) civil servants at the level of private secretary or above in the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills, have had with companies employing fewer than 50 employees since May.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kramer",,"Baroness Kramer","HL2430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419728","Cabinet Office","false","2015-10-19","<p>Lord Hart of Chilton entered the House in 2004 and made his maiden speech only after ceasing to be a ministerial special adviser in 2007. This approach, based on advice from the then Clerk of the Parliaments, has been accepted practice since then.</p>",,"Baroness Stowell of Beeston",,"2015-10-19T11:45:14.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419728/answer","Biography information for Baroness Stowell of Beeston","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419728/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419728/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-05","Peers: Ministerial Policy Advisers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Bridges of Headley on 22 September (HL2151), on what date the convention that peers who are ministerial special advisers do not speak on the floor of the House was first established.","false","Biography information for Lord Lexden",,"Lord Lexden","HL2431"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419729","Department of Health","false","2015-10-14","<p>NHS England has reviewed the action taken at East Kent University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. Due to an altercation between a member of the public and a member of the armed forces in uniform that had taken place the previous day, the employee concerned was acting in good faith, but handled the situation wrongly.</p><p>The Trust is absolutely clear that members of Her Majesty’s armed forces, whether in uniform or not, should not be treated differently to others. They have reinforced this policy to all members of staff and offered an apology to the patient involved for any embarrassment caused.</p><p>Additionally, NHS England is currently reviewing the East Kent University Hospitals Trust’s Equality and Diversity and Access Policies and will agree amendments if necessary. There are no plans to issue further guidance.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2015-10-14T14:28:37.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419729/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419729/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419729/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-05","Hospitals: Armed Forces","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what guidance, if any, they give to hospitals about whether patients may wear military uniforms in waiting and emergency rooms; what assessment they have made of the recent removal of a uniformed Royal Air Force sergeant from the waiting room of Queen Elizabeth The Queen Mother Hospital in Margate reportedly so as not to upset other patients from different cultures; and whether they plan to issue further guidance to hospitals about whether, in the light of that incident, patients who are members of the armed forces have the right to wear military uniforms in waiting and emergency rooms.","false","Biography information for Lord Maginnis of Drumglass",,"Lord Maginnis of Drumglass","HL2432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419730","Department for International Development","false","2015-10-14","<p>I am the Minister in DFID who has responsibility for ensuring that the particular vulnerabilities of lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender and intersex people are addressed through international development.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-10-14T16:00:25.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419730/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419730/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419730/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-10-05","Developing Countries: LGBT People","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government which Minister in the Department for International Development has responsibility for ensuring that the particular vulnerabilities of lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender and intersex people are addressed through international development.","false","Biography information for Baroness Northover",,"Baroness Northover","HL2433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419731","Department for International Development","false","2015-10-14","<p>A note describing “DFID’s approach on LGBT rights” will be published on the UK Government website by the end of 2015.</p>",,"Baroness Verma","HL2435","2015-10-14T16:13:07.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419731/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419731/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419731/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-10-05","Developing Countries: LGBT People","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the Department for International Development has published a LGBTI Strategy; and if so, where and when.","false","Biography information for Baroness Northover",,"Baroness Northover","HL2434"
